                        <div class="path-to-cert-content-summary">
                            <h2 class="section-heading"> Steps to get CAPM certified </h2>
                            <p style="display:inline;">Strengthen your knowledge and practice of project management processes and concepts with PMIÂ® certifications. Validate your expertise as a project manager with the CAPMÂ® certification and take advantage of networking opportunities&nbsp;with the best in the industry. Not sure where to start with your CAPMÂ® certification? Just follow these simple steps.</p><span class="view-more-link">.....</span> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="view-more-link">View more</a>
                            <div class="view-more-data editor-content" id="path-to-cert-data" style="display:none;">
                                <p><b>1. Get trained &nbsp;</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Confirm your eligibility to appear for the CAPM Certification Exam before proceeding.&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Register on the PMIÂ® website, or become a PMIÂ® member and member of your local chapter.&nbsp;<br></li>
                                    <li>Undertake 23 hours of CAPMÂ® Training from an Authorized Training Partner (ATP) like KnowledgeHut to earn 23 PDUs (PMIâs Education requirement).&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>2. Take the CAPM exam&nbsp;</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Check out the CAPMÂ® classroom training schedules &amp; dates to find a suitable session that meets your requirements.&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Sign up for the CAPMÂ® Exam by filling the PMIÂ® application form and submit it to PMIÂ® for approval.&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Once your online application has been determined to be complete, PMI will send your eligibility code, requesting payment.&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Pay the credential fee payment ($225 for PMI members; $300 for non-members).&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Schedule your CAPM exam on the PMIÂ® app, my.pmi.org; you can choose to take the exam at a Pearson VUE test center or via the online proctored testing solution.&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Develop a detailed study plan and study hard; study the PMBOKÂ® Guide Sixth Edition thoroughly along with the domains of risk management, as it is one of the primary references for the Exam.&nbsp;</li>
                                    <li>Appear for the exam with the required documents. Attempt the 150 multiple-choice questions exam in 3 hours.&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>3. Become a Certified Associate in Project Management&nbsp;</b></p>
                                <p>On passing the exam, youâll receive a congratulatory email from PMI, typically in about a week or two, after which you will see your name updated in the PMI registry. You're now CAPM certified!&nbsp;</p>
